chy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>X</mi><msub><mo>√ó</mo><mi>P</mi></msub><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f^*(A) = X \\times_P A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.688696em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">‚àó</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">√ó</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Does this help?</p>",
        "id": 242317870,
        "sender_full_name": "Jens Hemelaer",
        "timestamp": 1623402057
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh wow! Yes that helps. That equivalence looks so fun <span aria-label=\"stuck out tongue\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f61b\" role=\"img\" title=\"stuck out tongue\">:stuck_out_tongue:</span>, I wonder if there‚Äôs an intuitive explanation of what it ‚Äúmeans‚Äù in term of sets and functions in Set...</p>",
        "id": 242327406,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Smith",
        "timestamp": 1623407729
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Well it just means that inverse images preserve sums and quotients.</p>",
        "id": 242331456,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1623410617
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If you interpret pullback as base change (i.e. shifting from one over category regarded as a relative universe of discourse to another over category) then the stability of a property under pullback tells you something very strong about it - namely that it's 'absolute' or 'universal' (i.e. it doesn't depend on the base space over which you're working).</p>",
        "id": 242331707,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1623410795
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I meant something intuitive like how David Spivak explains pullbacks and pushouts in terms of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Olog\">his ‚Äúologs‚Äù</a>. An explanation in terms of everyday concepts, rather than more math <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span>.</p>\n<p>The ‚Äúbase change‚Äù perspective sounds interesting though. I need to read more into it. Is this discussed in simple terms in any books?</p>",
        "id": 242332175,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Smith",
        "timestamp": 1623411123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hmm, I'm not sure about any simple books. I think the first step is convincing yourself that for a set <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>, you have an equivalence of categories between the functor category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mtext>Set</mtext><mi>X</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{Set}^X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.914561em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Set</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.914561em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1362300000000003em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and the slice category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>Set</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{Set}/X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>. This idea that you can parametrise in two different ways (forwards via indexing and backwards via preimages) is a pretty important one.</p>",
        "id": 242332444,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1623411324
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Its a pretty inocuous idea at first sight but leads to all kinds of interesting mathematics (like the Grothendieck construction on presheaves, fibred categories, stacks, etc...)</p>",
        "id": 242332639,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1623411459
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I suppose a good book for this kind of thing is 'Generic Figures and Their Glueings' which deals with simple examples of presheaf categories.</p>",
        "id": 242333000,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1623411698
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ooh I haven‚Äôt heard of that book. I‚Äôll check it out!</p>",
        "id": 242333532,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Smith",
        "timestamp": 1623412069
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Interestingly I can‚Äôt find a single review or discussion of ‚ÄúGeneric Figures and their Glueings‚Äù online. Seems to be open access though. Has anyone else read it? Is it a well-written book? üòá</p>",
        "id": 242415006,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Smith",
        "timestamp": 1623454212
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just finished a reading group on this book. We got to chapter 11 before deciding to stop because of summer and the following review (most opinions were shared):</p>\n<p>The content of this book is nice to see as a first intro to topos theory because it has lots of examples and pictures that can convey intuition about presheaf toposes. However, it is presented in a very different way from the rest of the literature and no effort is made to make connections between their way and the standard way. While their way was relatively helpful for understanding the presheaf examples, I found it lost its edge when we arrived at more abstract stuff (adjoints and internal logic). Here are other issues that make the presentation so poor that I would not recommend reading it.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>There are several times where they refer to concepts defined later in the book with no warning.</li>\n<li>There are several symbols they use but do not define.</li>\n<li>There isn't enough explanations about how the theory is developed.</li>\n<li>I found the proofs way drier than I am used to in category theory (that may be true about topos theory in general for me, idk).</li>\n<li>The typography is very bad.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>All in all, if you want to get comfortable working with presheaf categories, I could suggest to read the first 6 chapters and do the exercises and complete the proofs to do actual computations. If you are more interested in toposes in general, do not bother.</p>",
        "id": 242416794,
        "sender_full_name": "Ralph Sarkis",
        "timestamp": 1623456566
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh wow! Thank you for that detailed review! I‚Äôll treat the book with caution then. I‚Äôll probably explore the first few chapters as you suggest.</p>",
        "id": 242417807,
        "sender_full_name": "Nick Smith",
        "timestamp": 1623458041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"405946\">Nick Smith</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/Distributive.20laws.20in.20Cartesian.20closed.20categories/near/242314794\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/locally+cartesian+closed+category\">nLab says that</a> in a locally Cartesian closed category \"pullbacks preserve all colimits\". Does this mean <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi><msub><mo>√ó</mo><mi>P</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>Y</mi><msub><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></msub><mi>Z</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>‚âÖ</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><msub><mo>√ó</mo><mi>P</mi></msub><mi>Y</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><msub><mo>+</mo><mi>Q</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><msub><mo>√ó</mo><mi>P</mi></msub><mi>Z</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X \\times_{P} (Y +_{Q} Z) \\cong (X \\times_{P} Y) +_{Q} (X \\times_{P} Z)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">√ó</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.036108em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.328331em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">Q</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚âÖ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">√ó</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.036108em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.328331em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">Q</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\"><span class=\"mbin\">√ó</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">Z</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span>, for all pullbacks and pushouts? </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's not what it <em>means</em>, but it does imply some sort of isomorphism like that.   (Jens fixed it.)</p>\n<p>If you're trying to check this in the category of sets, it's easier to check that pullbacks preserve coproducts and coequalizers.... since you can build pushouts from coproducts and coequalizers.</p>",
        "id": 242420104,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1623461622
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think a good way to understand this is via the equivalence <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>P</mi><mo>‚âÉ</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mi>P</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{Set}/P \\simeq \\mathrm{Set}^P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">‚âÉ</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.914561em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Set</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.914561em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.1362300000000003em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>: a set over <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span> is equivalent to a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span>-indexed family of sets.  Under this equivalence, the pullback functor <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>f</mi><mo>‚àó</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f^*</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.688696em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mbin mtight\">‚àó</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is just reindexing, replacing a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">P</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span>-indexed family of sets <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>p</mi></msub><msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>‚àà</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(A_p)_{p\\in P}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.036108em;vertical-align:-0.286108em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15139200000000003em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.286108em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.328331em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">‚àà</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"v